org.apache.flink.api.common.state

类 StateDescriptor<S extends State,T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.flink.api.common.state.StateDescriptor<S,T>
  • 类型参数:
    S - The type of the State objects created from this StateDescriptor.
    T - The type of the value of the state object described by this state descriptor.
    所有已实现的接口:
    java.io.Serializable
    直接已知子类:
    AggregatingStateDescriptor, FoldingStateDescriptor, ListStateDescriptor, MapStateDescriptor, ReducingStateDescriptor, ValueStateDescriptor

    @PublicEvolving
public abstract class StateDescriptor<S extends State,T>
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    Base class for state descriptors. A StateDescriptor is used for creating partitioned State in stateful operations. This contains the name and can create an actual state object given a StateBinder using bind(StateBinder).

    Subclasses must correctly implement equals(Object) and hashCode().

        protected StateDescriptor(java.lang.String name,
                          java.lang.Class<T> type,
                          T defaultValue)
        Create a new StateDescriptor with the given name and the given type information.

        If this constructor fails (because it is not possible to describe the type via a class), consider using the StateDescriptor(String, TypeInformation, Object) constructor.

        参数:
        name - The name of the StateDescriptor.
        type - The class of the type of values in the state.
        defaultValue - The default value that will be set when requesting state without setting a value before.

      • getSerializer

        public TypeSerializer<T> getSerializer()
        Returns the TypeSerializer that can be used to serialize the value in the state. Note that the serializer may initialized lazily and is only guaranteed to exist after calling initializeSerializerUnlessSet(ExecutionConfig).

      • setQueryable

        public void setQueryable(java.lang.String queryableStateName)
        Sets the name for queries of state created from this descriptor.

        If a name is set, the created state will be published for queries during runtime. The name needs to be unique per job. If there is another state instance published under the same name, the job will fail during runtime.

        参数:
        queryableStateName - State name for queries (unique name per job)
        抛出:
        java.lang.IllegalStateException - If queryable state name already set

      • getQueryableStateName

        public java.lang.String getQueryableStateName()
        Returns the queryable state name.
        返回:
        Queryable state name or null if not set.

      • isQueryable

        public boolean isQueryable()
        Returns whether the state created from this descriptor is queryable.
        返回:
        true if state is queryable, false otherwise.
